    "narrative": "For the April 9 slate, the LawDog daily optimization prioritizes **Gleyber Torres** as our most viable offensive anchor. With a score of 51.25, **Gleyber Torres** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Abel (4.28 xERA) and the premium opportunity afforded by batting second, which elevates his projection despite a slight drag from the dynamic platoon adjustment. While **Gavin Sheets** (46.70) offers some stability in the six-hole against Herget, the matchup is tempered by Herget\u2019s respectable 3.69 xERA, placing **Gavin Sheets** squarely in the marginal tier. **Geraldo Perdomo** rounds out the active trio at 42.63; while he occupies a high-value third spot in the order, his utility is constrained by a difficult matchup against McLean, whose 3.04 xERA acts as a significant dampener on his run-production ceiling.\n\nOur bench decisions today are dictated more by circumstance than choice, as stars like **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Yainer Diaz** are sidelined due to team off-days. The most notable non-start is **Lawrence Butler**, who projected well at 55.27, but unfortunately finds himself on the pine as he is currently outside the confirmed MLB starting lineup. Had **Lawrence Butler** been locked into the five-hole as anticipated, he would have easily supplanted **Geraldo Perdomo** in the starting configuration. We continue to monitor the statuses of **Tyler Freeman**, **Bryson Stott**, **Will Smith**, **Taylor Ward**, **Matt Chapman**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Luis Arraez**, **Masyn Winn**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** for subsequent slates, as their versatility remains critical for navigating the scarcity of stolen bases and maintaining efficiency in our 5x5 Roto chase. No extreme weather flags are currently impacting these specific matchups, but managers should note that any late-arriving lineup changes for the bottom-third of our roster could necessitate a pivot to ensure we are maximizing our limited daily game caps.",
